: '
script-daemon @ /home/v/cv_website/bash/daemon:

#!/bin/sh

while true; do
  echo test >> /home/v/cv_logs;
  sleep 60;
done


unit @ /etc/systemd/system/cv_website.service:

[Unit]
Description=My daemon

[Service]
ExecStart=/home/v/cv_website/bash/update_d
Restart=on-failure

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target 

To start the demon you run
systemctl start mydaemon.service 

To start at boot you enable it
systemctl enable mydaemon.service

source:
https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/426862/proper-way-to-run-shell-script-as-a-daemon

'
